-- Nikkei June Futures, Options Contracts Settle at 8,613.40
-- B y   Y o s h i a k i   N o h a r a
-- 2012-06-08T00:20:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-08/nikkei-june-futures-options-contracts-settle-at-8-613-40.html
The settlement price for  Japan ’s
Nikkei 225 Stock Average futures and options contracts for June
delivery was fixed at 8,613.40, traders said.  The Nikkei 225 Stock Average fell 1.1 percent to 8,534.87
as of 9:19 a.m. in Tokyo. The gauge closed at 8,639.72
yesterday.  The settlement price, also known as the “special
quotation,” of Nikkei 225 options is calculated after all
stocks in the Nikkei 225 begin trading.  To contact the reporter for this story:
Yoshiaki Nohara in Tokyo at 
 ynohara1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
